Lab 7 - Zero Trust Let&rsquo;s enforce a Zero Trust networking approach where all inbound traffic to any applications is denied by default.
Add a default deny-all policy to the backend-apis-team workspace:
cat &lt;&lt; EOF | kubectl apply -f - apiVersion: security.policy.gloo.solo.io/v2 kind: AccessPolicy metadata: name: allow-nothing namespace: online-boutique spec: applyToWorkloads: - selector: namespace: online-boutique config: authn: tlsMode: STRICT authz: {} EOF Refresh the Online Boutique webpage (echo http://$GLOO_GATEWAY). You should see an error with message &ldquo;RBAC: access denied&rdquo;
